 Graaff-Reinet - Members of Graaff-Reinet Police Services on Thursday responded to an anonymous call and discovered the body of a murdered woman, near Graaff-Reinet. According to the Police Officials, they received an anonymous call at about 06.38, informing them of a blonde female lifeless body lying about 3km next to the N9 road direction Middleburg. "On arrival, the members found the said body of the blonde woman, nearly dressed in Blue jeans and blue shirt," described police spokesperson, Captain Bradley Rawlinson. "On doing further inspection of the body, police officers found an open wound on the side of decreased's head." He said that Graaff-Reinet Detectives are investigating case of murder and they are following up on all possible leads. "Anyone who might be able to assist with information about the Murder, may contact Detective Sergeant M Gcinisa on 083 301 8475 Caller may remain anonymous and all information will be treated with the strictest confidentiality." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 